  "doc_id": "11738",
  "text": "In the present work, we describe for the first time the chemical synthesis, disulphide bridge organization, 3-D solution structure and docking results of CoTX1, a member of a novel class of α-KTx toxins. CoTX1, which is folded according to a α/β-scaffold, is the first toxin cross-linked by three disulphide bridges that is shown to be active on both voltage-gated (K v 1.2) and calcium-activated (IKCa1) K + channels. Our work extends a previous study made by Selisko and co-workers in defining the pharmacological targets of CoTX1 [CITATION_1] . It was shown by these authors that CoTX1 inhibits Shaker B and mouse Kv1.1 channels. It will be of interest to evaluate the effects of CoTX1 on a still wider range of potential pharmacological targets in future experiments, including channels with different ionic selectivity.",
